        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>[About July &#8212;, 1824?]</p>
<p>Dear <persName>Austin</persName></p>

<p>Let me know how you are getting on in <placeName>Texas</placeName>I am sorry to hear
such very unfavorable reports of the state of your <placeName>settlement</placeName> had<pb n="869"/>
you kept up a constant correspondence with me when in <placeName>England</placeName>
all your wishes would have been accomplished since I had friends
who would have advanced all the cash requisite&#8212;Is the <placeName>Colony</placeName>
healthy or unhealthy or how would it be were the land cleared away
I shall expect a full detail of every thing openly and candidly since
it still may be in my power to render you some assistance in your
schemes What <placeName>Mines </placeName>have you? how do the <persName>Comanches </persName>behave?
and the <persName>Indians </persName>how is your grant made, of all you demand or
only a part is it full or not.&#8212;</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Sor Dn Este van F. Austin</persName> <placeName>Sn Antonio de Bejar</placeName></p>

<p>[Endorsed:] <persName>A G. Wavell</persName> <placeName>Mexico </placeName><date n="xx-xx-1824">1824</date></p>


        </div1>
